en_172355_0	An asylum seeker has died on Manus Island, police have confirmed.
en_172355_1	"We had a suicide of a refugee at the Lorengau hospital in the early hours of this morning," Manus Island Police Commander David Yapu said.
en_172355_2	The Lorengau hospital is 25 kilometres from the detention centre where more than 700 male asylum seekers have been detained.
en_172355_3	The death is the second suicide on Manus in the past two months.
en_172355_4	The man, a Sri Lankan Tamil, is the sixth asylum seeker to die since Australia's offshore immigration detention centre in Papua New Guinea was re-opened four years ago.
en_172355_5	"We lost one more brother today," Ezatullah Kakar, a Pakistani asylum seeker wrote on Twitter.
en_172355_6	The Refugee Action Coalition's Ian Rintoul said there were no facilities on Lorengau to provide proper assistance to mentally distressed people.
en_172355_7	"The death has increased the anxiety and distress among all the refugees and asylum seekers on Manus as they struggle with their own circumstances," he said.
en_172355_8	"There are two other extremely mentally distressed people who urgently need assistance."
